(secondQuint)Flu Vaccine Responses in the Setting of Melanoma Treatment.

 Influenza vaccination is indicated for all adults, but the immunogenicity of vaccination has not been assessed in all situations.

 In particular, immune responses following influenza vaccination have not been studied in the setting of advanced melanoma and in the context of various anti-tumor treatments.

 In this study, we will look at the immune response of subjects receiving vaccination.

